What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?

Initializing a repository creates the files/directories that establish the configuration needed for subsequent git commands to work.

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository?
What value do you think it offers?
It indicates an intermediate area to place data specific to what we want to be part of the repository and not any temporary files. It helps unclutter the files of interest versus temporary, auto-generated binary files.

